  "signature": "ed25519:b4e2d1f3c5a7908e6d4b2f1a3c5e7d9b1f3a5c7e9d1b3f5a7c9e1d3b5f7a9c1e",
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation software (Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2) used under a validated installation with documented QA procedures, version control, and regression test suite. Required Gradation 2: documented QA plan with traceability.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2 deployed under ISO 9001-compliant QA framework. Installation qualification (IQ) and operational qualification (OQ) records on file. Regression test suite of 47 benchmark cases executed at each release update. Version-controlled input decks stored in Git repository with commit hashes linked to simulation outputs. Achieved level exceeds requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver correctness demonstrated via comparison to analytical solutions or published benchmark problems for structural mechanics. Required Gradation 2: at least one relevant benchmark with quantified error.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical verified against NAFEMS benchmark LE1 (plane stress) and LE10 (three-dimensional solid) with errors below 0.5% relative to analytical solutions. Additional verification against Timoshenko beam bending solution for slender rod geometry representative of the screw shank. All benchmark results documented in the code verification report."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study performed with Richardson extrapolation or GCI methodology. Required Gradation 3: systematic convergence study with quantified discretization uncertainty reported.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study conducted (coarse: ~85k elements, medium: ~220k elements, fine: ~580k elements) using hexahedral-dominant meshing of the screw-rod-vertebral body construct. Grid Convergence Index (GCI) computed per Roache methodology. GCI for stiffness QoI: 1.8%; GCI for yield force: 2.3%. Production mesh (medium) selected as balance between accuracy and computational cost. Discretization uncertainty incorporated into validation uncertainty budget."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver convergence verified with residual tolerance documented. Required Gradation 2: convergence criteria stated and residuals monitored.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear static analyses employ Newton-Raphson iteration with force residual tolerance 1e-4 and displacement residual tolerance 1e-5. Convergence achieved within 15 substeps for all 11 model instances. Energy residual monitored as secondary check; no solution accepted with energy residual above 1e-6. Solver logs archived for all production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation workflow reviewed by independent analyst. Required Gradation 2: independent review of model setup and boundary conditions documented.",
      "rationale": "Model setup, boundary conditions, contact definitions, and material assignments independently reviewed by a second analyst not involved in model construction. Review checklist completed and discrepancies resolved prior to production runs. Boundary conditions replicate ASTM F1717 fixture constraints: inferior vertebral body block fully fixed; superior block loaded through actuator pin in compression-bending configuration."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Physics representation assessed for appropriateness to COU. Required Gradation 3: documented justification of constitutive models and geometric assumptions with sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "Titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) modeled with bilinear isotropic hardening (E=114 GPa, sigma_y=880 MPa, E_t=1.5 GPa) based on certified material test reports from the device manufacturer. UHMWPE vertebral body blocks modeled as linear elastic (E=1.0 GPa) consistent with published F1717 surrogate data. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) at screw-rod interface. Sensitivity study on friction coefficient (0.1–0.3) showed <3% variation in stiffness QoI. Geometric fidelity confirmed by CT scan comparison of as-manufactured screws to CAD nominal."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric inputs traceable to measurements with uncertainty quantification. Required Gradation 3: inputs characterized with documented uncertainty bounds and propagation to QoI.",
      "rationale": "Material properties sourced from lot-specific tensile coupon testing (N=5 coupons per lot) per ASTM E8. Geometric dimensions measured by coordinate measuring machine (CMM) on 3 screws per lot; dimensional tolerances per device drawing applied as input uncertainty bounds. Monte Carlo uncertainty propagation (N=1000 samples) performed; combined input uncertainty contribution to stiffness QoI: ±3.1%. All input characterization records traceable to laboratory notebooks and instrument calibration certificates."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental samples representative of production device with documented traceability. Required Gradation 3: samples from production lots with full dimensional and material characterization.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested; all from production lots released under standard QMS procedures. Each construct fully characterized: screw dimensions by CMM, rod dimensions by optical comparator, material certificates on file. Sample allocation: 6 constructs at Lab 1 (FDA CDRH), 5 constructs at Lab 2 (DePuy Synthes). Inter-laboratory sample traceability maintained via unique serial numbers recorded in test reports."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of COU operating conditions. Required Gradation 3: multiple loading conditions or environmental conditions tested. Achieved Gradation 2: single standardized test condition (ASTM F1717 compression-bending only).",
      "rationale": "Testing conducted under ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration only. A single load angle (5 degrees from vertical per F1717 fixture geometry) was applied at a single displacement rate (25 mm/min). While F1717 also permits torsion testing, only compression-bending was in scope for this COU. The single-condition limitation is acknowledged; achieved level 2 is below the required level 3. This gap is accepted by the credibility assessment team given that compression-bending is the primary failure mode for this device and the COU is limited to this loading scenario."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model inputs matched to experimental conditions with documented equivalency mapping. Required Gradation 3: systematic parameter mapping with uncertainty in equivalency quantified.",
      "rationale": "Each of the 11 experimental constructs has a corresponding FEA model instance with inputs set to the measured values for that specific construct (as-measured dimensions, lot-specific material properties). Equivalency mapping table documented for all 11 construct-model pairs. Residual equivalency uncertainty (arising from unmeasured micro-geometric features) estimated at <1.5% contribution to QoI uncertainty via sensitivity analysis."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison of model outputs to experimental data with statistical validation metric. Required Gradation 3: validation metric computed with uncertainty and compared to pre-defined acceptance threshold.",
      "rationale": "Three QoIs compared: construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement. For each QoI, normalized error E/uval computed per ASME V&V 10.1 methodology combining experimental measurement uncertainty and model prediction uncertainty. Results: stiffness E/uval=1.31, yield force E/uval=1.74, force at 40 mm E/uval=1.52. All values below pre-defined threshold of 1.96 (95% confidence interval criterion). Percentage errors: 4.2%, 6.8%, 5.5% respectively, all below 10% threshold. Validation declared successful."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly linked to the clinical decision and COU. Required Gradation 3: documented traceability from QoIs to clinical endpoints and regulatory acceptance criteria.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness is a direct predictor of postoperative range of motion restriction and fusion success. Yield force predicts onset of permanent deformation and device failure risk. Force at 40 mm displacement characterizes post-yield energy absorption relevant to catastrophic failure assessment. All three QoIs are specified in ASTM F1717 as primary performance endpoints and are directly cited in FDA guidance for pedicle screw 510(k) submissions. Traceability matrix linking QoIs to clinical risk categories documented in the design dossier."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario matches COU in geometry, loading, material, and scale. Required Gradation 3: documented assessment of similarity between validation scenario and COU with quantified relevance.",
      "rationale": "Validation constructs are production-representative non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screws — the identical device geometry and material as the COU. Loading configuration (ASTM F1717 compression-bending) directly replicates the in vivo dominant loading mode for lumbar pedicle screws. Scale is 1:1 (no geometric scaling). The only departure from perfect COU relevance is the use of UHMWPE surrogate blocks rather than cadaveric bone; this is standard practice per F1717 and introduces known, bounded differences. Relevance assessment score: high. Achieved level meets requirement."
    }
  ],
